Today's significant market decline most likely marks the end of the oversold bounce from the June 4 th lows. The rally was based on little more than the hope of central bank rescues around the world in the face of what has now become a widely recognized global slowdown that threatens the onset of another recession. In our view the market faces a number of major headwinds including deteriorating economic conditions, a dimmer outlook for corporate earnings, the European solvency crisis and a major slowdown in China and other emerging nations.
